## When to use this component
Labels are paired with [inputs](/components/input), [textareas](/components/textarea), [radios](/components/radios), [checkboxes](/components/checkboxes), and [selects](/components/select) to describe a form input.

{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/label/examples/label/index.njk"})
}}

## How to use this component
Generally speaking you should not need to implement a label yourself as the form inputs have them imported in their respective templates.

All [input](/components/input) and [textarea](/components/textarea) components must have a visible label.

Do:
{{ 
    onsList({
        "items": [
            {
                "text": 'make sure the label is short, direct and written in sentence case'
            },
            {
                "text": 'left-align the label above the input'
            }
        ]
    }) 
}}

Do not:
{{ 
    onsList({
        "items": [
            {
                "text": 'use placeholder text to display a label because it will not be visible when the user clicks on the input'
            },
            {
                "text": 'place a colon at the end of the label'
            }
        ]
    }) 
}}

